snippet.title: Amber Heard's Me Too Toxic Love, If You Can't Handle Me at My Worst...
snippet.description:
Alex And Khelil discuss  toxic love and the infamous Marilyn Monroe quote, "If you can't handle me at my worst, you sure as hell don't deserve me at my best." 
Why is this quote so popular, particularly among women? Is it arrogant to expect someone to deal with your fatal flaws that you have no intention of fixing? Why would a grown person expect another to "handle" them? Is this just an excuse for toxic behavior?
